HEADWORD: Thunderhead
<hw>Thun"der*head`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A rounded mass
of cloud, with shining white edges; a cumulus, -- often appearing before
a thunderstorm.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Thundering</ent>⟦br⟧
